Parallel Computing Practice Repository  
Learn | Experiment | Benchmark  

---
English

This repository is dedicated to learning and experimenting with Parallel Computing concepts.  
It includes various examples written in C++ (with OpenMP, Pthreads, and more) that demonstrate how computation can be parallelized to achieve higher performance.

Each piece of code is clearly explained, focusing on understanding the core principles such as:

1. Thread creation and synchronization  
2. Data parallelism vs. task parallelism  
3. Performance measurement and benchmarking  
4. Cache efficiency and false sharing  
5. Load balancing and scalability

Over time, more examples will be added â€” from simple parallel loops to advanced concepts like distributed memory and GPU computing.

> Feel free to explore, learn, and contribute if youâ€™d like!  
> Each experiment here is part of an ongoing journey to better understand how computers think in parallel.

